#### Relevant publications:

###### [*Mechanisms of cardiac thermal tolerance in fish (led by Dr. Gail Schwieterman)*]{.underline}

-   Gail D. Schwieterman; **Emily A. Hardison**; Georgina K. Cox; Jacey Van Wert; Kim Birnie-Gauvina; Erika J. Eliason Mechanisms of cardiac collapse at high temperature in a marine teleost (Girella nigrians). Submitted to *Journal of Experimental Biology*.

###### [*Temperature and size on Barred Surfperch (led by Dr. Krista Kraskura)*]{.underline}

-   Krista Kraskura, **Emily A. Hardison**, Erika J. Eliason. Body size and temperature affect metabolic and cardiac thermal tolerance in fish. In review at *Scientific Reports*.

###### [*Temperature on Lobsters (led by Samantha Csik)*]{.underline}

-   Samantha R. Csik, Bartholomew P. DiFiore, Krista Kraskura, **Emily A. Hardison**, Joseph S. Curtis, Erika J. Eliason, and Adrian C. Stier (2023). The metabolic underpinnings of temperature-dependent predation in a key marine predator. *Frontiers in Marine Science*. doi: 10.3389/fmars.2023.1072807

